<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-18T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-18T16:00:00-05:00" n="412" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 614.119/103</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Leavell</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-18T17:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your September 12, 3 p.m. You may inform Guatemala Government that
                                when its Alien Property Custodian is given full authority to sell
                                the German property, the War Trade Board will be pleased to license
                                freely supplies for Empresa Electrica de Guatemala.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>